OL,4,CIreland would cost 20 billion euro
OL,5,Cover 20 years
OL,7,FSinn Fein has disputed the methodology
OL,8,Fof a report which suggested that a
OL,9,Funited Ireland would cost the Republic
OL,10,F20 billion euro for the next 20 years.
OL,12,FThe report, from the Institute of
OL,13,FInternational and European Affairs
OL,14,F(IIEA), revealed that the
OL,15,Freunification of Northern Ireland and
OL,16,Fthe Republic would require an increase
OL,17,Fin taxation and a significant
OL,18,Freduction in public expenditure.
